cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on Internet censorship and measurement techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of commercial VPNs as vantage points for measurements suggests a focus on network infrastructure (cs.NI). The detection of network interference such as surveillance and malware injection suggests a focus on cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) and system security (cs.SI). Finally, the use of clustering techniques to discover previously unknown block pages suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and data mining (cs.DM).
